From: Tom <tom@example.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 12:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix SMP use-after-free in chipidea UDC isr_tr_complete_low

isr_tr_complete_low() releases ci->lock (via spin_unlock(hwep->lock))
during the USB request completion callback. On SMP systems, another CPU
can take ci->lock during this window and call _ep_nuke(), which frees
requests and their TD nodes from the endpoint queue.

When the lock is re-acquired, list_for_each_entry_safe's saved next
pointer (hwreqtemp) may point to freed memory. Subsequent dereference
causes slab corruption detected by SLUB_DEBUG, followed by a crash in
the stack unwind path.

Fix by re-fetching the safe pointer from the list head after each
callback, ensuring we never iterate into freed entries.

Signed-off-by: Tom <tom@example.com>

diff --git a/drivers/usb/chipidea/udc.c b/drivers/usb/chipidea/udc.c
index 5f28aac85..4ff9decef 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/chipidea/udc.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/chipidea/udc.c
@@ -1283,6 +1283,15 @@ __acquires(hwep->lock)
 				hweptemp = hwep->ci->ep0in;
 			usb_gadget_giveback_request(&hweptemp->ep, &hwreq->req);
 			spin_lock(hwep->lock);
+			/* The endpoint queue may have been modified by another
+			 * CPU during the callback (ci->lock was released above).
+			 * Re-fetch the safe pointer from the list head to avoid
+			 * use-after-free on hwreqtemp.
+			 */
+			if (list_empty(&hwep->qh.queue))
+				break;
+			hwreqtemp = list_first_entry(&hwep->qh.queue,
+					struct ci_hw_req, queue);
 		}
 	}